         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0660">
               <p>A native of <placeName>Epworth, Lincolnshire</placeName>, Richard
                  (&apos;Dick&apos;) Ellison was baptized at the parish church by <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2188.xml"/>Samuel Wesley Sr</persName>.&apos;s
                  predecessor as rector on <date when="1690-08-09">Aug. 9, 1690</date>. He married
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2194.xml"/>Susanna Wesley Jr</persName>.
                  in <placeName>Ackworth, Yorkshire</placeName> on <date when="1718-01-11">Jan. 11,
                     1718</date>. The couple had at least ten children, of whom four lived to
                  adulthood. Ellison was a landowner of some means, but he had a temper and a
                  weakness for alcohol. He beat <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2194.xml"
                     />Susanna</persName> on more than one occasion, until she finally took the
                  children and moved to <placeName>London</placeName> about <date when="1735"
                     >1735</date>. The couple were eventually reunited in
                     <placeName>London</placeName>, and Ellison died there in <date when="1760-04"
                     >April 1760</date>. See Maser, <hi rend="italic">Sisters</hi>, 32–36.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
   </text>
